text: Englewood in March 2019. Englewood is an unincorporated community in Boone County, in the U.S. state of Missouri. ==History== A post office called Englewood was established in 1892, and remained in operation until 1906. The community was named after Englewood, Illinois. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Boone County, Missouri Category:Unincorporated communities in Missouri
